BLUETONGUE, BOVINE - ITALY (CUNEO, CREMONA)
*******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: 8 Sep 2006
From: Pablo Nart <pablo.nart@terra.es>
Source: Cybermed.it [translation summarized by P. Nart, edited]
<http://test.cybermed.it/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=11347&Item>

A 2 month old Italian press report mentions the detection by the Istituti
Zooprofilattici Sperimentali of an unspecified serotype of bluetongue virus
in 2 cows in the provinces of Cuneo and Cremona.
Map of Cremona:
<http://www.multimap.com/map/browse.cgi?lat=45.1335&lon=10.0261&scale=2000000&icon=x>.
Map of Cuneo:
<http://www.multimap.com/map/browse.cgi?lat=44.3888&lon=7.5471&scale=50000&icon=x>.
--
Pablo Nart
<pablo.nart@terra.es>
[Although this report is 2 months late, these regions have not previously in
2006 reported bluetongue virus. This moderator felt it important to cover
these regions despite the lateness of this report. - Mod.TG]
